            "description": "The President\u2019s Programme is a joint Russian-Dutch initiative dating from 1997, when prime ministers Kok and Chernomyrdin agreed that each year, 50 Russian managers from the private sector would be welcomed in the Netherlands for an educational program. This initiative has been successful throughout the last 15 years, and holds on to its purposes:\nDeveloping and strengthening economic bonds between Russia and the Netherlands;\nCooperation that leads to sharing knowledge about Russian and Dutch society, culture and economy.\nThe President\u2019s Programme is geared towards prosperous and profitable business relationships. To achieve this, the training is completely focused on preparing economic bonds between Dutch and Russian firms.\nBut the President\u2019s Programme goes beyond education, in the sense that all participants will be involved in an \u2018internship\u2019 in a Dutch firm for a three week period. This is not a standard internship; it is aimed at establishing economic bonds. The Russian manager and their Dutch host company work on finding opportunities for these economic bonds throughout the internship period. In the past, the internships have led to good spin-offs for the Dutch and Russian corporate worlds. Whether in the form of export or import contracts, dealer partnerships, research cooperation and foreign direct investments.\nThe President\u2019s Programme is facilitated by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs.",
